<plot>"Flower of a Girl" is a visual poem about a despondent woman who lies curled up on her bathroom floor, unable to rouse herself. She hears an echo of a laugh and searches the mirror, finding an image of her younger self. A tentative "hello" beckons her outside. Will she be able to get up off the floor?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?198246</url></doc>
